==Italian==
===Adverb===
'''ne'''

#from [[there]]
#:''Ne sono venuto'' &mdash; I have come from there

====Usage notes====
*The pronoun '''ne''' replaces "di là".
*:''Sono di Genova; ne sono venuto stamattina'' &mdash; I am from Genova; I came from there this morning

===Pronoun===
'''ne'''

#of it
#:''Ne ho sentito parlare'' &mdash; I have heard of it
#:''Cosa ne pensi?'' &mdash; What do you think of it?
#of them (''sometimes not translated in English'')
#:''C'è ne sono due'' &mdash; There are two (of them)
#''see usage notes''

====Usage notes====
*The pronoun '''ne''' stands for "di" + ''pronoun'', and so can be a translation of ''preposition'' + "it/them" for any preposition that is translated as "di" in Italian.

===See also===
*[[né#Italian|né]]
